$ /var/log/faillog

`/var/log/faillog` records failed login attempts.

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/var/log/wtmp, → Linux/fhs/var/log/lastlog, → Linux/fhs/var/log/btmp

  `/var/log/faillog` is the *failure login file*. This is a binary file. The content can be examined with → Linux/shell/commands/faillog.


  The → Linux/shell/commands/useradd#l[-l flag in useradd].

  → Linux/security/log-file[Security: log files]

